<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<worksheet>
  <title>Final Review, Part III</title>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <statement>
      <p>Suppose that <m>A</m> is a <m>3\times2</m> matrix and that
  <m>A\twovec10 = \threevec{-2}{1}4</m> and <m>A\twovec01 = \threevec11{-2}</m>.
  What is <m>A\twovec2{-3}</m>.</p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <introduction>
      <p>Suppose that <m>B</m> is a <m>2\times2</m> matrix and that
  <md>
  B\twovec23 = \twovec10,~~~B\twovec11 = \twovec01.
  </md></p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What is <m>B^{-1}</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Find a solution to the equation <m>B\xvec=\twovec4{-1}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What is the matrix <m>B</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <introduction>
      <p>Let <m>C</m> be the matrix
  <m>C = \begin{bmatrix}
    3 \amp 2 \amp 0 \\
    k \amp -1 \amp 1 \\
    1 \amp 2 \amp 2 \\
      \end{bmatrix}</m></p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>For what values of <m>k</m> is the matrix <m>C</m>
 invertible?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>For what values of <m>k</m> do the columns span <m>\real^3</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>For what values of <m>k</m> are the columns linearly independent?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What does it mean for <m>\vvec</m> to be an eigenvector of a matrix
  <m>A</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace=".5in">
      <statement>
        <p>Why do we only discuss eigenvectors for square matrices?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>For what value of <m>k</m> is <m>\lambda=3</m> an eigenvalue of the matrix
  <m>\begin{bmatrix}
    2 \amp 3 \\
    -2 \amp k
  \end{bmatrix}</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>For that value of <m>k</m>, find a basis for the eigenspace <m>E_3</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Suppose that <m>A</m> is a <m>2\times2</m> matrix having eigenvectors
  <m>\vvec_1 = \twovec21</m> and <m>\vvec_2=\twovec31</m> and eigenvalues
  <m>\lambda_1=4</m> and <m>\lambda_2=-2</m>.</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Write the vector <m>\twovec10</m> as a linear combination of
  eigenvectors.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Find the vector <m>A\twovec10</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1.5in">
      <statement>
        <p>In the same way, write the vector <m>\twovec01</m> as a linear
  combination of eigenvectors.  Then find the vector <m>A\twovec01</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What is the matrix <m>A</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Is <m>A</m> diagonalizable?  If so, find the matrices <m>P</m> and <m>D</m> and
  verify that <m>A=PDP^{-1}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

</worksheet>
